n common, but out of what divides them. Society of Others, the first anthropological book about the Korowai, offers a picture of Korowai lives sharply at odds with stereotypes of "tribal" societies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aEthnologyzIndonesiazPapua. 0aEthnopsychologyzIndonesiazPapua. 0aKinshipzIndonesiazPapua. 0aMourning customszIndonesiazPapua. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aanthropology.  aattachment.  aavoidance.  achild rearing.  achildbearing.  acontact and separation.  acreation of belonging.  adeath.  adisruption.  aethnography.  afamily.  ahuman relations.  aindonesia.  aindonesian culture.  aindonesian society.  akin.  akinship.  akorowai of west papua.  aliving far apart.  amarriage.  amourning.  aotherness.  aplace ownership.  arelatives.  ashared experiences.  asmall scale societies.  asocial organization.  asocial ties.  asociality.  aspatial margins.  atragedy.  atree house dwellings.  atrial society.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052025685940uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094332240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520943322423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520943322/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY